race.comment: NAINA (3) wasn't disgraced in city class second-up off a near miss at Ballarat. Won't find this assignment as tough and has been kept up to the mark with a Flemington jumpout. Fitter again and a bold showing expected. ON BROADWAY (4) resumed and finished just a half a length from the winner over 1600m at Tatura after racing on the pace. Must raise the bar again, but with the extra fitness she can threaten. FINALE (6) hasn't won for more than a year but has pieces of form that would see her feature. She just missed here three back at this level and can't be taken lightly. BON FETE (5) peaks today and is still well shy of her best. Has been giving away starts but has a key gear addition and is worth keeping onside.
